.TH YTRAN 1 "2026-03-08" "ytran 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ytran \- fetch and summarize YouTube video transcripts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ytran
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ VIDEO_URL_OR_ID " ..." ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ytran
fetches YouTube video transcripts via transcriptapi.com, formats them
with Claude, generates summaries, and stores everything in a local
SQLite database.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-browse
Open an interactive browser for the transcript database after processing
any URLs given on the command line.
If invoked with no arguments,
.B \-\-browse
is implied.
Options and URLs may be intermixed in any order.
.TP
.B \-\-fix
Scan all database entries and fill in any missing fields (metadata,
transcripts, summaries).
Entries saved with
.B \-\-no\-summary
are skipped unless
.B \-\-force
is also given.
.TP
.B \-\-force
When combined with
.BR \-\-fix ,
also process entries that were saved with
.BR \-\-no\-summary .
The raw\-only flag is cleared and summaries are generated.
.TP
.BI \-\-model " MODEL"
Claude model to use for formatting and summarization.
Default: claude-sonnet-4-5.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-no\-summary
Fetch metadata and raw transcript only; do not format or summarize
with Claude.
The entry is flagged as raw\-only so that future
.B \-\-fix
runs leave it alone.
Does not require an Anthropic API key.
.TP
.BI \-\-skip " ID1,ID2,..."
Comma-separated list of video IDs to skip during \-\-fix operations.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/ytran/youtube-transcripts.db
Default database location (respects $XDG_DATA_HOME).
.TP
.I ~/.youtubetotranscript_api_key
transcriptapi.com bearer token.
.TP
.I ~/.anthropic_api_key
Anthropic API key for Claude.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ytchan (1)
\(em download transcripts for an entire YouTube channel.
Passes
.B \-\-no\-summary
by default; accepts additional
.B ytran
options before the channel URL.
Requires
.BR yt\-dlp .
